node.contents: The error occurs because there are 2 transactions working on the same record. If a record is read by 2 transactions, and if the record is saved by one transaction first, an optimistic locking exception is thrown in the second transaction, because the system assumes that nobody else is going to modify the record.

  2. Retry the transaction: Make sure that no non-transactional state is kept between the retries.
